- [The Investigation](home_court_investigation.html): the tests behind the findings, with p-values and confidence intervals.
- [Regression Results](home_court_results.html): the full statistical output, tables and coefficients.
- [Stats Explainer](home_court_stats_explainer.html): a plain guide to the methods used.
- [Stats Tutorial](../../generated/stats_tutorial.html): worked examples that reproduce the key results by hand.

**About this series.** Most of the writing here is Claude's; I go back and forth with it until the prose is clear enough that I understand it.
The analysis underneath is Python running standard methods, not the language model: Claude interprets the results, but does none of the math.
I've spent dozens of hours pushing it to be clearer, and I still find that faster than writing it all myself.
It won't read like a human wrote every line, but I hope the intent comes through.
